Hey people, anyone has an idea if there is a faster algorithm than this to do matrix multiplication? (and have in mind that im not talking about big matrices, they are f64 but the matrices are small (less than a hundred m, n)):
```c
void mtx_dot(u16 am, u16 an, f64 *a, u16 bn, f64 *b, f64 *out) {
    u16 i, j, k;
    for (i = 0; i < am; i++) {
        for (j = 0; j < bn; j++) {
            out[i * bn + j] = 0;
            for (k = 0; k < an; k++) {
                out[i * bn + j] += a[i * an + k] * b[k * bn + j];
            }
        }
    }
}
```

